{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"a1035ad0-179b-4489-a0b8-d0a3acfc7777","content":"**Use `dotnet workload update`.**\n\n- **`dotnet workload update`** — Downloads and installs the latest versions of all installed workloads to match your current SDK. After a .NET SDK update, this is what you need to bring workloads (like `maui`) back in sync.\n\n- **`dotnet workload repair`** — Re-installs workloads *at their current versions*. It fixes corrupted installs but doesn't upgrade anything. If the problem is a version mismatch with a newer SDK, this won't help.\n\n**Quick fix:**\n```bash\ndotnet workload update\ndotnet build\n```\n\nIf the issue persists after updating, check which workloads are installed with `dotnet workload list` and ensure `maui` (or `maui-android`, `maui-ios`, etc.) is present.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"a041b01a-4576-42b2-9eb8-f18795646a13","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about .NET MAUI workload management — specifically whether to use `dotnet workload update` or `dotnet workload repair` after a SDK update broke their build. This is a general knowledge question, not a codebase task.","outputTokens":268,"requestId":"1442:3F1DAE:6D1E76B:75617D4:6A03CBBF"},"id":"b2210eb6-b26c-4509-a13c-3b943434edc2","timestamp":"2026-05-13T00:54:31.579Z","parentId":"39b819bf-5437-4498-83fd-b1957ab1c04f"}
